
// This Hyperlambda code checks if the current user has the "root" role using [auth.ticket.in-role]. If true, it adds nodes from [.arguments/arguments] to the input of [sockets.signal], sends a signal to "magic.workflows.action" for the "root" role with specified arguments, and sets the current date and time to [.time]. Key slots include [add] for adding nodes, [unwrap] for evaluating expressions, [sockets.signal] for sending signals, and [set-value] for setting the current date and time.
if
   auth.ticket.in-role:root
   .lambda
      add:x:./*/sockets.signal/*/args/*/input
         get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/arguments/*
      unwrap:x:+/**
      sockets.signal:magic.workflows.action
         roles:root
         args
            type:action
            name:x:@.arguments/*/name
            input
      set-value:x:@.time
         date.now
